{'contentformat': 'text/x-wiki', 'contentmodel': 'wikitext', '*': '{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Water}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Water|prevnum=727|prev=Incineroar|nextnum=729|next=Brionne|roundleft=tl|roundright=tr}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Disambig|species=Popplio}}\n|}\n{{Pokémon Infobox\n|name=Popplio\n|jname=アシマリ\n|tmname=Ashimari\n|ndex=728\n|type1=Water\n|category=Sea Lion\n|height-ftin=1\'04"\n|height-m=0.4\n|weight-lbs=16.5\n|weight-kg=7.5\n|adex=007\n|abilitylayout=2\n|ability1=Torrent\n|abilityd=Liquid Voice\n|egggroupn=2\n|egggroup1=Water 1\n|egggroup2=Field\n|eggcycles=15\n|evtotal=1\n|evsa=1\n|expyield=64\n|lv100exp=1,059,860\n|gendercode=31\n|color=Blue\n|catchrate=45\n|body=03\n|pokefordex=popplio\n|generation=7\n|friendship=70\n}}\n\'\'\'Popplio\'\'\' ([[List of Japanese Pokémon names|Japanese]]: \'\'\'アシマリ\'\'\' \'\'Ashimari\'\') is a {{type|Water}} {{OBP|Pokémon|species}} introduced in [[Generation VII]].\n\nIt [[Evolution|evolves]] into {{p|Brionne}} starting at [[level]] 17, which evolves into {{p|Primarina}} starting at level 34.\n\nAlong with {{p|Rowlet}} and {{p|Litten}}, Popplio is one of three [[starter Pokémon]] of [[Alola]] available at the beginning of [[Pokémon Sun and Moon|Pokémon Sun, Moon]], [[Pokémon Ultra Sun and Ultra Moon|Ultra Sun, and Ultra Moon]].\n\nAlong with {{p|Rowlet}} and {{p|Litten}}, it was the second [[Generation VII]] Pokémon to be revealed to the public on May 10, 2016.\n\n==Biology==\nPopplio is a {{wp|pinniped}} Pokémon that is primarily blue. It has large eyes, a long, white snout with black whiskers, and round, pink nose. There is a small, rounded earflap on each side of its head. Around its neck is a light blue ruff, which extends past its shoulders. It has four flippers. The front flippers are larger than the hind, and have white markings separating its toes.\n\nPopplio is able to snort bubbles of water from its nose, which it uses as part of its battle strategy. On land, it uses the elasticity of its bubbles to perform acrobatic stunts and jumps. It practices daily with increasingly larger water bubbles. It can swim at 25 mph (40 km/h)<ref>[http://www.pokemon-sunmoon.com/en-us/pokemon/popplio/ Pokémon Sun and Moon site | Popplio]</ref>\n\n==In the anime==\n[[File:Lana Popplio.png|thumb|left|250px|Popplio in the {{pkmn|anime}}]]\n===Major appearances===\n====[[Lana\'s Popplio]]====\nPopplio debuted in \'\'[[SM001|Alola to New Adventure!]]\'\' as {{an|Lana}}\'s main Pokémon. It evolved into Brionne in \'\'[[SM106|Evolving Research!]]\'\', and again into Primarina in \'\'[[SM120|The One That Didn\'t Get Away!]]\'\'.\n\n===Minor appearances===\nA Popplio briefly appeared alongside a {{p|Rowlet}} and {{p|Litten}} in \'\'[[M20|I Choose You!]]\'\'.\n\nA {{pkmn|Trainer}}\'s Popplio appeared in a flashback in \'\'[[SM100|Battling the Beast Within!]]\'\' as a resident of what is now the [[Ultra Ruin]].\n\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Animedexheader|Alola}}\n{{Animedexbody|SM005|Popplio|Rotom Pokédex|Popplio, the Sea Lion Pokémon. A {{t|Water}} type. Popplio can control water balloons, and works hard so it can make bigger balloons.}}\n{{Animedexfooter/Pokémon|\'\'Sun & Moon\'\'|Alola}}\n\n==In the manga==\n[[File:Hau Popplio Adventures.png|thumb|200px|Popplio in [[Pokémon Adventures]]]]\n===In the Pokémon Adventures manga===\nPopplio debuted in \'\'[[PASM02|The Delivery of Rotom and the Girl]]\'\', under the ownership of [[Professor Kukui]]. In \'\'[[PASM16|A Photoshoot and the Abandoned Thrifty Megamart]]\'\', he was revealed to have given it to [[Hau]]. It later evolved into {{p|Brionne}} and eventually further into {{p|Primarina}}.\n{{-}}\n\n==In the TCG==\n{{main|Popplio (TCG)}}\n\n==Game data==\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Dex/Header|type=Water}}\n{{Dex/NA|gen=VII}}\n{{Dex/Gen/2|gen=VII|reg1=Alola|num1=007|reg2=Kanto}}\n{{Dex/NE|[[Pokémon: Let\'s Go, Pikachu! and Let\'s Go, Eevee!|Let\'s Go, Pikachu! and Let\'s Go, Eevee!]]\u200e}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Sun|entry=This Pokémon snorts body 